rComments: He doesn't post the slides because he believes it helps attendance but it's counter effective because no one listens since we're all scrambling to copy the slides. Otherwise, he's pretty helpful if you approach or email him, and he provided all the short stories via pdf. The midterm and Final aren't too hard if you review his outlines

Not the greatest lecturer. Speaks quite low and fast. He makes his own comments for each lecture slide, but does not keep the slide up after he's finished making his comment. This would be fine if he posted his lecture slides online, but he doesn't. Nice effort in getting students to attend class, but really unsuccessful due to his lecturing method

Really encourages you to go to class by not posting lecture notes online. I really liked his lectures because he tried to engage the students through small activities (you get participation marks). You can tell he really tries hard with his lectures and he definitely knows what he is talking about.
Teacher tries to put in a good effort making the material interesting, but his monotone voice and lackluster powerpoint classes do not give Canadian Literature a good representation.
